pects military action within days. Western Iran contains the bulk of the country’s nuclear, missile and air-defence infrastructure, including sites in Natanz, Fordow, Arak and Kermanshah that have been targeted repeatedly since the war began on February 28.\\n\\nIranian airspace has technically been classified as closed under international aviation safety advisories since the start of the war, but the new NOTAM formalises the most extensive restrictions in weeks. Reports from Tehran also flagged unusual Iranian Air Force movement, including fighter jet sorties from Mehrabad.\\n\\nQuestion box captured on the same page states: 'Fact: Iran's Civil Aviation Authority issued NOTAM OIIX A1010/26 on May 22, shutting all airports in the western part of the Tehran Flight Information Region. The restrictions came into effect on May 22 and remain valid until May 25, 2026.' It also states: 'Fact: Only 8 airports remain operational, including Tehran's Mehrabad and Imam Khomeini International, alongside Isfahan, Shiraz, Yazd, Tabriz, Mashhad and Bandar Abbas. Flights are restricted to daylight hours and require fresh per-flight approval from the Civil Aviation Authority.'\\n\\n[plaintiff] PX-R1 raw NOTAM confirms timing and west Tehran FIR closures\\nTitle: All west Tehran FIR airports are closed except listed airports operating sunrise to sunset, with new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights. - OIIX NOTAM | Notamify\\nURL: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/693f2d0f-54d3-433b-8128-49f5475ba269\\nRetrieval: 2026-06-30T13:00:05Z\\n\\nVisible page text captured:\\n\\nA1010/26\\nEST\\nAD Airport Operations\\n\\nAll west Tehran FIR airports are closed except listed airports operating sunrise to sunset, with new CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights.\\n\\n2026-05-22 20:46 - 2026-05-25 08:30\\nAge: AGING Issued 38 days ago\\nDuration: SHORT 3 days EST\\n\\nPeriod of Applicability\\nUTC\\n2026-05-22 20:46 - 2026-05-25 08:30\\n\\nInterpretation\\nAll a