ing operations in the airspace\n\nBased on the record evidence, I need to determine whether this meets the definition of \"major closure\" from the market's rule text:\n\n\"A 'major closure' is defined as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian Airspace region.\"\n\nThe NOTAM OIIX A1010/26 specifically states that \"ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR ARE CLSD\" with very limited exceptions, and all previous permissions were suspended. While the defense correctly identifies it as \"airport operations\" restriction, closing all airports in the western sector of Tehran FIR fundamentally impacts commercial flight operations in that region - arrivals, departures, and by extension, operations transiting through that airspace.\n\nThe rule text explicitly notes that \"Limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting (e.g. exceptions for certain flights pre-approved by the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority may be permitted).\" The NOTAM created limited exceptions by requiring fresh CAA approval and limiting operations to daylight hours, which fits this provision.\n\nThe NOTAM was effective from 2026-05-22 20:46 UTC to 2026-05-25 08:30 EST, which includes May 24th. The context from both reporting sources indicates this was for security reasons, not weather. Also, it was clearly an action initiated by Iran's own aviation authorities.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5258c4c006624891b3d78074","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM OIIX"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM OIIX","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3-coder-